# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov
.env.test.dev
.env.test.prod

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file (for local API keys during testing)
.env
.env.test
.env.local

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/

# macOS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

logs/*.jsonl

# Compiled binary
context-gateway

# Internal test scripts (not for public release)
tests/manual/
docs/internal/

# AI assistant / planning docs
CLAUDE.md
Tool-discovery-rework.md

# Context-Gateway specific
#.claude/
logs/
*.log
*.pid
bin/
benchmarks/results_summary/
benchmarks/results_detailed/

# Dev container (personal testing)
Dockerfile.dev
benchmarks/runs/
benchmarks/backup/
# benchmarks/notebooks/

# Python
benchmarks/src/__pycache__/*
*.pyc
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.build/
docs/*
!docs/quickstart/
.aider*
.gocache/
.gomodcache/

web/dashboard/node_modules/
web/dashboard/dist/
web/dashboard/.vite/

# Plugins
internal/plugins/openclaw/node_modules/

.claude/
